    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this shortfall is mitigated by the conservative 10% QoI acceptance threshold and the direct structural nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10%. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
